  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Living Conditions of Displaced Populations in North-East Nigeria Through Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) and Shelter Assistance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to address congestions in camps and worsening living conditions due to the rainy season and support beneficiary-driven governance structures through camp coordination and camp management and shelter and non-food items interventions in and out of camps to improve the living conditions of crisis-affected populations in five Local Government Areas (LGAs) in Borno and Adamawa states in Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
